A career at Arup offers you the chance to make a positive difference in the world. Independently owned and independently minded, Arup is the creative force at the heart of many of the world’s most prominent projects in the built environment. We offer a broad range of professional services that combine to make a real difference to our clients and the communities in which we work. We are truly global, and our 15,000 planners, designers, engineers and consultants around the world deliver innovative projects with creativity and passion.
About you

Recognised relevant tertiary qualifications in 3rd level qualification, degree or equivalent experience in a business or technical systems related area;
Relevant industry experience in Cyber Security or Industrial Control Systems within a consulting business environment;
Membership of relevant professional institutions/professional peer bodies and relevant certifications/qualifications (such as CISSP, CISM, CCSP, CWSP, CRISC, SABSA);
The ability to apply and explain cyber security frameworks such as IEC62443, ISO27001, NIST Critical Infrastructure and NCSC CAF.
Demonstrate extensive knowledge of specialist areas and keeps up to date with current industry information and own knowledge and skills
About the role
Experienced in working with clients while collaborating with local subject matter experts and their global Cyber Security advisory peers. The increasing digitalisation of the built environment presents unique Cyber Security challenges for our clients.

About the role

Manage key projects for the business, delivering quality protective engineering design and interacting with the other discipline leaders on projects.
Work with clients to understand and address cyber security risks and create sustainable and innovative solutions;
Assist in the development of world class capabilities within the region including staffing, processes, tools and frameworks;
Act collaboratively with similar leaders in other Arup Regions to share experience, capability and resources for best Global effect;
