Program Manager – Cyber Security
 About us
 Saab Australia is a defence, security and cyber solutions provider, specialising in the development and integration of major defence and security systems. For over 30 years in Australia, we have built a reputation for delivering complex systems integration projects that provide proven and advanced capabilities to keep us ahead of today’s challenges.
 From combat, communications, security and underwater systems, to mixed reality, cyber security and deployable health solutions, our extensive portfolio of products and services provide high-technology solutions for defence forces and civil industries across the globe.
 Apply today to join our crew and deliver solutions with purpose.
 The role
 As part of our Professional Services group, the Program Manager (Cyber Security) will be responsible for the management and continued growth of the Cyber Security Professional Services consulting business within Saab Australia, providing a suite of Cyber Security and Risk Advisory related services across government and industry; as well as supporting Saab Australia’s project initiatives and internal requirements.
 Working with the Cyber Security Professional Services team, you will utilise your knowledge, experience, leadership and business development skills to set the strategic direction for this business team and align with Saab Australia’s Corporate Strategy to drive ongoing business growth.
 Further, the successful candidate will:

 Lead and manage the development and review of the Cyber Security Professional Services Business Strategy, aligned with the Saab Australia Corporate Security Strategies;
 Ensure suitable engagement with all stakeholders, for increased awareness of the Cyber Business strategic management approach and timetables;
 Provide leadership, advice, guidance and support to develop the Cyber Security Professional Services team, Saab staff, clients as well as Saab’s Cyber Security and Risk consulting line of business;
 Supervising, mentoring and motivating members of the Cyber Security Professional Services team to enhance the delivery of Professional Services;
 Overseeing commercial performance of the Cyber Security Professional Services Program including liaison with commercial, legal, finance, procurement and other relevant stakeholders
 Develop campaign and capture plans to secure key government and industry sector markets;
 Identify new market domains, segments and opportunities for the cyber business;
 Develop campaign and capture plans to secure key government and industry sector markets;
 Identify new market domains, segments and opportunities for the cyber business;

 Flexible work arrangements such as hybrid work from home / office, 9 day fortnight will be considered for this role.
 About you
 Your skills and experience will include:

 Leadership and management capabilities, cultivating a strong collaborative culture and productive team dynamics;
 Planning and leading the growth of a professional services based team delivering technology or governance based outcomes;
 Experience in program and project management, with the ability to manage multiple projects, timelines and budgets concurrently;
 Demonstrated stakeholder engagement and management skills (with the client, project delivery teams and the business)
 Strong business acumen including sales, financial and commercial skills and experience;
 Broad knowledge and experience across various information security domains and technologies with industry certifications including: IRAP, CISA, CISM. (desirable)

 A Defence security clearance is required for this role, applicants must be Australian citizens and eligible to obtain and maintain an NV1 clearance.
 Culture and benefits
 We employ over 600 Australians and are committed to fostering a culture of excellence and enriching the employee experience.
 By joining Saab, you’ll be a part of a collaborative and supportive organisation, where your professional growth and work-life balance are emphasised. You’ll work within an innovative and vibrant workplace, while having the opportunity to develop a long-term, fulfilling career.
 For further information about at career at Saab, visit the page adjacent: https://www.saab.com/markets/australia/careers/saab-life
 Applications
 Click ‘Apply’ to submit your CV and cover letter in support of your application. You may contact our careers team at careers.mailbox@au.saabgroup.com for a copy of the full position description. Kindly observe that this is an ongoing recruitment process and in exceptional circumstances, the position might be filled before the closing date of the advertisement. We encourage applications as early as possible to avoid disappointment.
 Saab Australia is an Equal Opportunity Employer and encourages Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islanders to apply. We also welcome applications from individuals with culturally diverse backgrounds. 
Saab Australia is a proud supporter of the Veterans’ Employment Program and welcomes the interest of ex-service members, veterans and their families.
